def _get_grouper(
    obj,
    key=None,
    axis=0,
    level=None,
    sort=True,
    observed=False,
    mutated=False,
    validate=True,
):
    group_axis = obj._get_axis(axis)

    if isinstance(key, list):
        groupings = []
        exclusions = []

        for col in key:
            if col in obj:
                if validate:
                    obj._check_label_or_level_ambiguity(col)
                groupings.append(
                    Grouping(
                        group_axis,
                        obj[col],
                        obj=obj,
                        name=col,
                        level=level,
                        sort=sort,
                        observed=observed,
                        in_axis=True,
                    )
                )
                exclusions.append(col)
            else:
                raise KeyError(col)

        grouper = BaseGrouper(group_axis, groupings, sort=sort, mutated=mutated)
        return grouper, exclusions, obj
